---
layout: layouts/component-demo.njk
title: Switch Button
description: a toggle switch for turning a setting on or off
---

{% from "components/switch-button/macro.njk" import switchButton %}

<h2>Off (default)</h2>
<p>
  <label for="sw-1">Email notifications</label>
  {{ switchButton({ id: "sw-1", label: "Email notifications" }) }}
</p>

<h2>On</h2>
<p>
  <label for="sw-2">SMS reminders</label>
  {{ switchButton({ id: "sw-2", label: "SMS reminders", checked: true }) }}
</p>

<h2>Disabled</h2>
<p>
  <label for="sw-3">Push notifications</label>
  {{ switchButton({
    id: "sw-3",
    label: "Push notifications",
    disabled: true
  }) }}
</p>

<h2>When to use</h2>
<p><code>SwitchButton</code> uses <code>role="switch"</code>, which
  screen readers announce as "switch, on" or "switch, off". Use
  for explicit on/off settings where the state is the point. For
  "action in effect" semantics (Bold / Italic / Mute), prefer
  <a href="/components/toggle-button/"><code>ToggleButton</code></a>.</p>
